ersations about education reform nothing was off the table we had heated debates about the role of racism classism and opportunity gaps in affecting student achievement we discussed the importance of teacher policies school management district accountability and political elections despite our blazing passion for results we acknowledged that the needle has not shifted much in the last two decades i remain inspired however as ambitious organizations across the country including studentsfirst have pushed education reform to the forefront of the american conscience change will come there is simply no alternative but what about the rest of the world what about india first things first we can surely take a page out of the book of education pioneers we need great people to make great things happen an education pioneers colleague reminded us in our closing session education is the civil rights issue of our generation one day your grandchildren will ask you when schools were failing all around you where were you and what did you choose to do i believe it is also the human rights issue of our generation so i hope all you smart people out there with so much passion save a little room in your hearts for education reform and i hope that i am doing my part and that soon enough all children will receive a great education including in india and other parts of the world supriya balsekar summer intern for studentsfirst post new comment subject comment input format filtered html web page addresses and e mail addresses turn into links automatically allowed html tags a em strong cite code ul ol li dl dt dd lines and paragraphs break automatically full html web page addresses and e mail addresses turn into links automatically you may use swf file song mp3 to display flash files inline more information about formatting options captcha this question is for testing whether you are a human visitor and to prevent automated spam submissions math question 1 3 solve this simple math problem and